'''Cristian Volpato''' (born 15 November 2003) is an Australian professional football player who plays as an [[Attacking Midfielder|attacking midfielder]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{Italian football updater|Sassuolo}} club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] and the [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]].

== Early life ==
Volpato was born in [[Camperdown, New South Wales|Camperdown]],<ref name=":11">{{Cite web|last=Carina|first=Stefano|date=2021-10-26|title=Roma, Mourinho convoca il 17enne Volpato, il primo della scuderia di Totti|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/sport/calcio/roma_mourinho_convoca_17enne_volpato_primo_scuderia_di_totti-6282588.html|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[Il Messaggero]]|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028082213/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/sport/calcio/roma_mourinho_convoca_17enne_volpato_primo_scuderia_di_totti-6282588.html |archive-date=28 October 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Zucchelli|first=Chiara|date=27 Oct 2021|title=Dalla scuderia Totti col 10 sulle spalle. Roma, la prima di Volpato|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Roma/27-10-2021/roma-prima-convocazione-volpato-chi-ragazzo-primavera-4202091467824.shtml|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=it-IT|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211027150008/https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Roma/27-10-2021/roma-prima-convocazione-volpato-chi-ragazzo-primavera-4202091467824.shtml |archive-date=27 October 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":8">{{Cite web|last=Bergantini|first=Luca|date=5 Apr 2021|title=Christian Volpato, un Aussie nella città eterna|url=http://www.mondoprimavera.com/news/329803795974/focus-christian-volpato-un-aussie-nella-citt-agrave-eterna|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=MondoPrimavera|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415072737/https://www.mondoprimavera.com/news/329803795974/focus-christian-volpato-un-aussie-nella-citt-agrave-eterna |archive-date=15 April 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|last=Federici|first=Thomas|date=4 December 2021|title=Résultat et résumé AS Rome - Inter Milan, Serie A, 16e journée|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/championnat-d-italie/2021-2022/as-rome-inter-milan-live/519327|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211205005510/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/championnat-d-italie/2021-2022/as-rome-inter-milan-live/519327 |archive-date=5 December 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Cardia|first=Ivan|date=1 Nov 2021|title=Roma, Mourinho punta ancora sulla Primavera: i prossimi cinque talenti da lanciare|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/roma-mourinho-punta-ancora-sulla-primavera-i-prossimi-cinque-talenti-da-lanciare-1603815|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=TUTTOmercatoWEB|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211101165120/https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/roma-mourinho-punta-ancora-sulla-primavera-i-prossimi-cinque-talenti-da-lanciare-1603815 |archive-date=1 November 2021 }}</ref> a [[Suburb (Australia)|suburb]] of the [[Inner West|Inner West]] in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]].<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|date=14 September 2021|title=Cristian Volpato is set to tear it up for AS Roma – and possibly turn his back on Australia|url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2021/09/15/cristian-volpato-is-set-to-tear-it-up-for-as-roma-and-possibly-turn-his-back-on-australia/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=[[The Roar (website)|The Roar]]|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210915091612/https://www.theroar.com.au/2021/09/15/cristian-volpato-is-set-to-tear-it-up-for-as-roma-and-possibly-turn-his-back-on-australia/ |archive-date=15 September 2021 }}</ref> He attended the prestigious rugby school [[St Joseph's College, Hunters Hill]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sjcobu/status/1468161669167681537|title=x.com}}</ref> Volpato is of [[Italian Australians|Italian descent]], with both his parents being second generation Italians.

== Club career ==

=== Youth career ===
Volpato first started playing football in [[Abbotsford, New South Wales|Abbotsford]], in [[Sydney]] [[List of Sydney suburbs|suburbs]], where he was a prolific goalscorer.<ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|last=Paoli|first=Alessandro|date=5 Dec 2021|title=Esordio in A per Volpato. Il 10 italo-austrialiano nel segno di Totti|url=https://www.vocegiallorossa.it/approfondimenti/esordio-in-a-per-volpato-il-10-italo-austrialiano-nel-segno-di-totti-218304|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-05|website=Voce Giallorossa|publisher=TUTTOmercatoWEB|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211205105329/https://www.vocegiallorossa.it/approfondimenti/esordio-in-a-per-volpato-il-10-italo-austrialiano-nel-segno-di-totti-218304 |archive-date=5 December 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|last=Raso|first=Emilio|date=2021-02-26|title=Volpato: "Che emozione lavorare con Dzeko, Pedro e Mkhitaryan"|url=https://www.ilromanista.eu/news/settore-giovanile/77017/volpato-ache-emozione-lavorare-con-dzeko-pedro-e-mkhitaryana|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=Il Romanista|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227065112/https://www.ilromanista.eu/news/settore-giovanile/77017/volpato-ache-emozione-lavorare-con-dzeko-pedro-e-mkhitaryana |archive-date=27 February 2021 }}</ref>

This allowed him to take his first steps into professional football, at [[Andrea Icardi]]'s [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] Soccer School, [[Sydney FC]] and the [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]] academy.<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" /><ref name=":7">{{Cite web|last=Lewis|first=Dave|date=19 May 2020|title=Meet the Roma-based Aussie who's been snapped up by Totti|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sport/football/article/2020/05/19/meet-roma-based-aussie-whos-been-snapped-totti|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211206025007/https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sport/football/article/2020/05/19/meet-roma-based-aussie-whos-been-snapped-totti |archive-date=6 December 2021 }}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|last=Davidson|first=John|date=23 Feb 2021|title=Aussie teenager signs pro deal with Roma|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sport/football/article/2021/02/23/aussie-teenager-signs-pro-deal-roma|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207104952/https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sport/football/article/2021/02/23/aussie-teenager-signs-pro-deal-roma |archive-date=7 December 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Symonds |first1=Nick |title=The next Socceroos golden generation |url=https://www.theroar.com.au/2021/03/07/the-next-socceroos-golden-generation/ |access-date=29 January 2022 |work=The Roar |date=6 March 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-09-28|title=Football NSW squads ready for National Youth Championships|url=https://footballnsw.com.au/2016/09/29/football-nsw-squads-ready-for-national-youth-championships/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[Football NSW]]|language=en-AU|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207111507/https://footballnsw.com.au/2016/09/29/football-nsw-squads-ready-for-national-youth-championships/ |archive-date=7 December 2021 }}</ref> He soon earned a trial in the [[A.S. Roma Youth Sector|AS Roma Youth Sector]] through [[Fabrizio Piccareta]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":6" /><ref name=":9">{{Cite web|last=Andrea Di Carlo|date=2021-09-13|title=Volpato, numero 10 "benedetto" dal Capitano|url=https://www.siamolaroma.it/2021/09/13/volpato-numero-10-benedetto-dal-capitano/|access-date=2021-12-05|website=Siamo la Roma|language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Bossi|first=Dominic|date=2021-09-16|title=Cut by Wanderers but selected for Italy: How Sydney kid slipped from Australia's grasp|url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/cut-by-wanderers-but-selected-for-italy-how-sydney-kid-slipped-from-australia-s-grasp-20210916-p58sd5.html|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210916195517/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/cut-by-wanderers-but-selected-for-italy-how-sydney-kid-slipped-from-australia-s-grasp-20210916-p58sd5.html |archive-date=16 September 2021 }}</ref>

After a few months in [[Rome]] where he was able to demonstrate his attacking abilities, the young footballer signed a three-year contract with the club from the [[Italian capital]] in January 2020.<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":7" /><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Rugari|first1=Vince|last2=Bossi|first2=Dominic|date=2020-01-23|title=Macarthur FC hit one Mile-stone, but losing hope of reaching another|url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/macarthur-fc-hit-one-mile-stone-but-losing-hope-of-reaching-another-20200123-p53u2n.html|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123184610/https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/macarthur-fc-hit-one-mile-stone-but-losing-hope-of-reaching-another-20200123-p53u2n.html |archive-date=23 January 2020 }}</ref><ref name=":10">{{Cite web|date=21 Jan 2020|title=Roma scatenata sul mercato! Ecco Cristian Volpato|url=https://www.gazzettaregionale.it/under-17/2020/01/21/news/roma-scatenata-sul-mercato-ecco-cristian-volpato-92090/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=Gazzetta Regionale|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211209195031/https://www.gazzettaregionale.it/under-17/2020/01/21/news/roma-scatenata-sul-mercato-ecco-cristian-volpato-92090/ |archive-date=9 December 2021 }}</ref> A month later he also joined [[Francesco Totti]]'s agency, while he had already taken the number 10 shirt with [[A.S. Roma Youth Sector|Roma's Youth]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":7" /><ref name=":9" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Rupolo|first=Nicholas|date=19 Feb 2020|title=The Mixer: Francesco Totti to sign Aussie starlet|url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/the-mixer-francesco-totti-to-sign-aussie-starlet-538226|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=FTBL|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222114746/https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/the-mixer-francesco-totti-to-sign-aussie-starlet-538226 |archive-date=22 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-08-06|title=Totti, presa la procura del giovane Cristian Volpato|url=https://www.ilromanista.eu/football-please/news/50411/foto-totti-presa-la-procura-del-giovane-cristian-volpato|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=IlRomanista.eu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919033833/https://www.ilromanista.eu/football-please/news/50411/foto-totti-presa-la-procura-del-giovane-cristian-volpato |archive-date=19 September 2020 }}</ref>

A year later, Volpato signed his first professional contract with Roma, a new three-year deal tying him to the club until 2024.<ref name=":5" /><ref name=":6" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-23|title=Roma, Volpato rinnova fino al 2024: "Incredibile allenarsi con Dzeko, Mkhitaryan e Pedro"|url=https://www.romanews.eu/roma-volpato-rinnova-fino-al-2024-incredibile-allenarsi-con-dzeko-mkhitaryan-e-pedro/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=Roma news|language=it-IT|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211209194634/https://www.romanews.eu/roma-volpato-rinnova-fino-al-2024-incredibile-allenarsi-con-dzeko-mkhitaryan-e-pedro/ |archive-date=9 December 2021 }}</ref> As the youth competitions due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Italy]], he then became a regular with the under-18, scoring five goals during the [[2020–21 A.S. Roma season|2020–21 season]], soon earning a place in the under-19s squad.<ref name=":11" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name=":9" />

=== Roma ===
Volpato made his professional debut for [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] on 4 December 2021, aged 18, in a [[Serie A]] match lost 3–0 against [[Inter Milan]].<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Canicchio|first=Lorenzo|date=4 Dec 2021|title=Esordio in Serie A per Cristian Volpato. Giornata comunque memorabile per lui|url=https://www.gazzettaregionale.it/home/2021/12/04/news/esordio-in-serie-a-per-cristian-volpato-un-giorno-comunque-memorabile-124627/|url-status=live|access-date=7 December 2021|website=Gazzetta Regionale|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211204185650/https://www.gazzettaregionale.it/home/2021/12/04/news/esordio-in-serie-a-per-cristian-volpato-un-giorno-comunque-memorabile-124627/ |archive-date=4 December 2021 }}</ref> On 19 February 2022, Volpato scored his first Serie A goal in a match drawn 2–2 against [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Chi è Volpato, il talento gestito da Totti a segno in Roma-Verona {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/chi-e-volpato-talento-gestito-da-totti-a-segno-in-roma/bltfc272aa1f010b80f|access-date=2022-02-20|website=www.goal.com}}</ref>

In the [[2022–23 Serie A|following season]], after making his debut in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] with Roma, he made his first league appearance on 31 October 2022, coming on as a substitute for [[Nicolò Zaniolo]] at the 57th minute of the match against Hellas Verona. In the occasion, he scored a goal and assisted [[Stephan El Shaarawy]] for another one, thus helping Roma obtain a 3–1 win.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Ottaviano |first=Luca |date=2022-10-31 |title=Roma, da Verona a Verona: il filo giallorosso di Volpato |language=it |work=MondoPrimavera |url=https://www.mondoprimavera.com/news/101667212806/roma-da-verona-a-verona-il-filo-giallorosso-di-volpato |access-date=2022-11-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rotondaro |first=Vittorio |date=2022-11-01 |title=Chi è Volpato, il talento gestito da Totti a segno due volte contro il Verona |url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/chi-e-volpato-talento-gestito-da-totti-a-segno-in-roma-verona/bltfc272aa1f010b80f |access-date=2022-11-01 |website=Goal.com |language=it}}</ref>

=== Sassuolo ===
After stalling for much of negotiation,<ref>{{cite web |title=Accordo Roma-Sassuolo per Volpato: 9 milioni alla 'Lupa', ma il giocatore temporeggia {{!}} Goal.com Italia |url=https://www.goal.com/it/notizie/accordo-roma-sassuolo-volpato-9-milioni-giocatore-temporeggia/blt2ca4342630dac454 |website=Goal Italia |language=it |date=12 June 2023}}</ref> on 29 June 2023, Volpato signed a contract to [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Calciomercato {{!}} Cristian Volpato è un nuovo calciatore neroverde |url=https://www.sassuolocalcio.it/in-evidenza/calciomercato-cristian-volpato-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-neroverde/ |website=U.S. Sassuolo Calcio |language=it-IT |date=29 June 2023}}</ref> after completing a €7.5 million [[Transfer (association football)|transfer]] which included a 15% future resale fee.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marzio |first1=Gianluca Di |title=Sassuolo, ufficiali gli acquisti di Volpato e Missori dalla Roma |url=https://gianlucadimarzio.com/it/sassuolo-volpato-missori-roma-calciomercato-news-29-giugno-2023 |website=Gianluca Di Marzio |language=it}}</ref> The transfer is the third-highest fee for an Australian player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Teen prodigy seals third-biggest Aussie transfer ever as Socceroos locked in Italy tug of war |url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/socceroos/football-news-2023-transfers-socceroos-cristian-volpato-leaves-roma-for-sassuolo-latest-stats/news-story/fd503c6cc49e5ebce475bd98e8177443 |website=Fox Sports |language=en |date=29 June 2023}}</ref>

Volpato scored his first goal for Sassuolo against Bologna on 3 February 2024.{{Citation needed|date=May 2026}}

== International career ==
Born in Australia, Volpato is a dual citizen of both Australia and Italy.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Austin |first1=Jack |title='Bitter taste' could see Socceroos miss out on future superstar Cristian Volpato |url=https://sport.optus.com.au/news/gegenpod-podcast/os39181/cristian-volpato-as-roma-jose-mourinho-australia-socceroos-italy-nationality-gegenpod |website=Optus Sport |access-date=11 June 2023}}</ref> He is eligible to represent either [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia]] or [[Italy national football team|Italy]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lewis |first1=Dave |title='He loves Australia': AS Roma starlet ready to commit to Socceroos |url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/he-loves-australia-as-roma-starlet-ready-to-commit-to-socceroos-576518 |website=FTBL |date=2 March 2022}}</ref>

=== Italy ===
In early August 2021, Volpato was called by [[Carmine Nunziata]] to the [[Italy national under-19 football team|Italy national under-19 team]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=|date=2021-08-06|title=First match of the season on 13 August against Albania: Nunziata selects 25 Azzurrini|url=https://www.figc.it/en/national-teams/news/first-match-of-the-season-on-13-august-against-albania-nunziata-selects-25-azzurrini/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=[[Federazione Italiana Giuoco Calcio]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210806091513/https://www.figc.it/en/national-teams/news/first-match-of-the-season-on-13-august-against-albania-nunziata-selects-25-azzurrini/ |archive-date=6 August 2021 }}</ref> being however forced to forfeit a few days later.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Paoli|first=Alessandro|date=8 Aug 2021|title=Forfait El Hilali, Volpato e Zanotti. Convocati Cavallini e Giovane|url=https://www.tuttonazionali.com/under-19/forfait-el-hilali-volpato-e-zanotti-convocati-cavallini-e-giovane-15026|url-status=live|access-date=2021-12-07|website=Tutto Nazionali|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211205113620/https://www.tuttonazionali.com/under-19/forfait-el-hilali-volpato-e-zanotti-convocati-cavallini-e-giovane-15026 |archive-date=5 December 2021 }}</ref> He took part in the [[2022 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] with Italy U19, scoring two goals in the tournament.{{citation needed|date=November 2022}} On 19 November 2022, he made his debut for the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]] squad in a friendly match lost 4–2 against [[Italy national under-21 football team|Germany]].{{citation needed|date=July 2024}} In June 2024, he took part in the [[Maurice Revello Tournament]] in France with Italy.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.tournoimauricerevello.com/smartphone/festival/archives/joueurs.php?annee=2024| title=Festival International Espoirs Football Tournoi Maurice Revello Toulon| publisher=Maurice Revello Tournament| website=tournoimauricerevello.com| language=fr| accessdate=14 May 2025}}</ref>

