| source = – [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]] manager [[Graham Arnold]] on Volpato declining the offer to represent Australia at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]
}}
On 12 December 2021, it was reported that [[Australia men's national soccer team|Australia national team]] manager [[Graham Arnold]] was considering calling up Volpato for the upcoming [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]] and [[Oman national football team|Oman]]. He was also called up to the [[Australia men's national under-23 soccer team|Australia U23]] side; however, he was withdrawn from the squad by Roma.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/football/socceroos/football-news-2021-socceroos-cristian-volpato-to-be-offered-senior-cap-for-australia-serie-a-as-roma-italy-national-team-interest/news-story/547605b061b26aa88a089c5e2e1ab5b2?fbclid=IwAR0abYmyqhazpnk1fhZg1IzO9eS1bFumMtt34bRnrxYBajAWjjKD6dzidiA|title = Socceroos' plot to hand shock cap to Serie a prodigy Cristian Volpato, to avoid losing him to Italy|date = 12 December 2021}}</ref> In March 2022, following Australia's 2–0 loss to [[Japan national football team|Japan]], Volpato posted an image on his [[Snapchat]] story poking fun at the team. This led to many fans labeling him as "childish" and "immature".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/online-trolls-driving-roma-starlet-away-from-socceroos-578356|title=Online trolls 'driving' Roma starlet away from Socceroos|first=Dave|last=Lewis|newspaper=FTBL|date=6 April 2022}}</ref> With Australia announcing their World Cup squad on 8 November, Graham Arnold disclosed that Volpato had been offered a spot in the 26-man squad, but declined the opportunity.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Cristian Volpato declined to play for Socceroos at World Cup, says Australia coach Graham Arnold |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/au/soccer/news/cristian-volpato-socceroos-world-cup-italy-australia-graham-arnold/w6jv9zxvgs4l1rbxzixnskdc |access-date=2022-11-08 |website=www.sportingnews.com |date=8 November 2022 |language=en}}</ref>

In May 2026, Volpato was called up for Australia's [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]] squad, effectively ending debate over his national team selection.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2026-05-29 |title=Socceroos boosted as young midfielder switches allegiance from Italy |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2026-05-29/fifa-world-cup-2026-socceroos-land-striker-in-shock-switch/106739466 |access-date=2026-05-29 |work=ABC News |language=en-AU}}</ref> On 6 June, Volpato made his debut for Australia, starting in a friendly against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] that ended in a 1–1 draw. He was substituted at half-time and replaced by [[Connor Metcalfe]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=tpellizzeri |date=2026-06-06 |title=Socceroos share Swiss spoils in final friendly |url=https://aleagues.com.au/news/australia-friendly-world-cup-switzerland-match-report/ |access-date=2026-06-07 |website=A-Leagues |language=en-AU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2026-06-07 |title=Australia turns its attention to FIFA World Cup after practice games |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2026-06-07/time-for-australia-s-fifa-world-cup-campaign-to-begin/106769422 |access-date=2026-06-07 |work=ABC News |language=en-AU}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Volpato is able to play both as a ''[[trequartista]]'' or a [[Winger (football)|winger]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> Seen as a ''regista'' or [[deep-lying playmaker]] in his early career,<ref name=":10" /> he is often compared to [[Francesco Totti|Totti]], his model as a number 10 and his direct mentor in his first year at [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":4" /><ref name=":7" /><ref name=":9" />

